  </body>
</html>


Explanation :

1.var userInput = prompt("Enter your name:");: 
This line displays a pop-up dialog box in the user's browser with the message "Enter your name:". The user is expected to type in their name and click "OK" or press "Enter."

2.if (userInput !== null && userInput.trim() !== "") {: This line begins an "if" statement. It checks whether the value stored in the userInput variable is not null (meaning the user didn't click the "Cancel" button on the pop-up) and whether the input, after removing any leading or trailing spaces using .trim(), is not an empty string.
3.Inside the "if" block:
var inputname = "Hello " + userInput + " Welcome To World of JavaScript";: This line creates a new string by combining the text "Hello," the user's input (their name), and "Welcome To World of JavaScript." The resulting string is stored in the inputname variable.

console.log(inputname);: This line outputs the content of the inputname variable to the browser's console. 
